    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dsas-annual-report-and-accounts-2011-12"/>
    <title>DSA's annual report and accounts 2011 to 2012</title>
    <category>Publication</category>
    <summary>The Driving Standards Agency's (DSA’s) performance over the financial year, including how it met its service standards and other targets.</summary>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;h2 id="summary"&gt;Summary&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This report accounts for &lt;abbr title="Driving Standards Agency"&gt;DSA&lt;/abbr&gt;’s performance over the financial year, including the extent to which &lt;abbr title="Driving Standards Agency"&gt;DSA&lt;/abbr&gt; met its service standards and financial targets. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It’s structured around &lt;abbr title="Driving Standards Agency"&gt;DSA&lt;/abbr&gt;’s business plan for the respective year and its key priorities for the year. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This report is addressed to:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;government ministers&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;the Department for Transport&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;other government departments and agencies&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;driving organisations&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;the media&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;the general public&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
&lt;abbr title="Driving Standards Agency"&gt;DSA&lt;/abbr&gt; employees&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;“The maintenance and integrity of the Driving Standard Agency website is the responsibility of the Accounting Officer; the work carried out by the auditors does not involve consideration of these matters and accordingly the auditors accept no responsibility for any changes that may have occurred to the financial statements since they were initially presented on the website.”&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
