  <entry>
    <id>tag:www.gov.uk,2005:PublicationesquePresenter/16264</id>
    <published>2012-04-02T01:00:00+01:00</published>
    <updated>2012-11-09T14:31:12+00:00</updated>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dsas-business-plan-2012-13"/>
    <title>DSA's business plan 2012 to 2013</title>
    <category>Publication</category>
    <summary>The measures, outcomes and key programmes that the Driving Standards Agency aims to deliver during 2012 to 2013.</summary>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;In 2012 to 2013, our main priorities will be to:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;offer candidates a theory test appointment within 2 weeks of their preferred date, and keep 99.5% of those appointments&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;offer candidates a car driving test appointment within 9 weeks of their preferred date, and keep 98% of those appointments&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;improve our customer satisfaction&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;increase the take-up of digital services to 85%&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;cut carbon emissions by improving efficiency of our buildings, and by not travelling or travelling in greener ways where possible&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;comply with the EU third driving licence directive by providing tests for new categories of motorcycles from 19 January 2013, and starting a periodic training programme for all driving examiners&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;launch an online service for businesses to book and manage practical driving tests and manage their business with us so they don’t have to do this by phone or post&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
