  <entry>
    <id>tag:www.gov.uk,2005:PublicationesquePresenter/17407</id>
    <published>2011-03-31T01:00:00+01:00</published>
    <updated>2012-11-30T14:29:01+00:00</updated>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dsas-carbon-management-plan"/>
    <title>DSA carbon management plan</title>
    <category>Publication</category>
    <summary>This plan sets out the Driving Standards Agency's (DSA's) vision and targets for reducing carbon emissions by 2016.</summary>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;In March 2011 the government published a new set of environmental commitments. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The carbon management plan commits &lt;abbr title="Driving Standards Agency"&gt;DSA&lt;/abbr&gt; to a target of reducing &lt;abbr title="Carbon Dioxide"&gt;CO2&lt;/abbr&gt; by 25% by 2016, which would allow &lt;abbr title="Driving Standards Agency"&gt;DSA&lt;/abbr&gt; to make potential savings of £2.2 million.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;abbr title="Driving Standards Agency"&gt;DSA&lt;/abbr&gt; has worked with the &lt;a rel="external" href="http://www.carbontrust.com" title="Carbon Trust"&gt;Carbon Trust&lt;/a&gt; to develop this 5-year carbon management plan. It sets out &lt;abbr title="Driving Standards Agency"&gt;DSA&lt;/abbr&gt;’s vision, baseline, target, projects, funding, governance and communications support. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Throughout the 5-year period &lt;abbr title="Driving Standards Agency"&gt;DSA&lt;/abbr&gt; will monitor performance and update the plan.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
